      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Hutt Street, Adelaide ¶ 27th April 1892 ¶ Baron Von Mueller K.C.M.G. Ph D MD. &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c ¶ Melbourne ¶ Dear Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.04.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From David Lindsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.200/3, folder 5, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Hutt Street, Adelaide</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27th April 1892</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller K.C.M.G. Ph D MD. &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have intended writing you for sometime past, and have really had so much writing to do that I have put it off from time to time until I feel that now an apology is due to you for want of courtesy shown you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope ere long to have an opportunity of chatting with you on the subject of the breakup of the Elder Expedition,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Elder Scientific Exploring Expedition, 1891-2, broke up in disarray near Geraldton, WA, in January 1892 when all but one of the scientific members of the party resigned. See Lindsay (1893) and Feeken, Feeken &amp; Spate (1970), pp. 200-2.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a result which I know has caused you a great deal of pain, and disappointment — to me it has been the severest blow I ever experienced — and I hope you clearly understand it is no fault of Sir Tho Elder — he has not changed his mind or regretted the expenditure, nothing of the sort. I do not care to write what I could tell you, but I hope what you have heard from Mr MacDonald<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A. C. Macdonald?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will have given you a fair idea of the trouble.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When you have the whole of the evidence before you, you will see the almost<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">impossible</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>part I had to fill, and what bad material my party was composed of. I am extremely glad to be able to say that Mr Helms<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Richard Helms, surveyor and third in charge on the expedition. See also R. Helms to M, 4 October 1891.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>collections of botanic specimens could not have been eclipsed by any one for he was an indefatigable worker — his whole heart was in the work but dear me what a fearful temper he has, the least thing would send him off into a frightful passion. Still that could be dealt with better than the underhand sneaking actions of Leech<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F. W. Leech, second in command on the expedition.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and the Dr.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably F. J. Elliott, medical doctor and photographer on the expedition.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Had we been permitted to continue our work, 18 months more would have completed the grandest exploration ever made in Australia.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You sir must be terribly disappointed as I know your dearest wish has been to discover some relics of Leichardt,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Leichhardt.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and MacPhee's<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alexander McPhee reported meeting Aborigines at Lagrange on the NW coast of Australia who told him of a party of white men who had perished one by one in the sandy wastes, some days' walk SE of Joanna Spring. See D. Lewis (2006).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>account renders it probable enough that something might have been found between the Oakover<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Oakover River, WA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and Lake MacDonald.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I too would have given<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>much to have settled the mysterious and interesting question as to what became of that brave but unfortunate explorer.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The winding up of the expedition was carried out with such indecent haste that there was no opportunity of altering the decision. We have travelled about 2250 miles in new country and mapped down about 80,000 square miles so that the results of the expedition are by no means insignificant.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hoping that you are still blest with good health and sympathising with you in the worry caused by the impecuniosity of the Victorian Govt</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I am faithfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>David Lindsay</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
